s this process with regard to the history of graphic design and based on two case studies.  afunded by Schweizerischer Nationalfonds  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 10. Jan 2022) 4aDesignforschung. 4aDesignrhetorik. 4aRhetorische Gestaltungstechniken. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Rhetoric.2bisacsh  aRhetoric of design.  adesign research.  arhetoric design techniques.2 aSchweizerischer Nationalfondsefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2021 Part 1z978311075070608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2022 Part 1z978311076682008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2021z9783110753899oZDB-23-DKU0 cEPUBz97831106810480 cprintz978311067723240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110680942zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110680942zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110680942/original  a978-3-11-075070-6 DG Plus DeG Package 2021 Part 1b2021  a978-3-11-076682-0 DG Plus DeG Package 2022 Part 1b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2021  aZDB-23-DKUb2021  aZDB-23-GOA